| Feature | Rationale |
|--------|-----------|
| **0-indexed attempts** | Standard in backoff literature; `attempt=0` → first retry delay |
| **Full jitter on cap** | Jitter applied *after* capping the exponential value (AWS spec) |
| **AbortSignal-aware wait** | Prevents hanging during shutdowns or cancellations |
| **No exponential growth on capped delay** | Ensures `delay ≤ capMs` always |
| **Default cap 5s** | Reasonable for most APIs (adjustable) |
| **Throw last error** | Standard promise-returning retry pattern |

